      "comment": {
        "comments": [
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12928506/comment/15530564",
            "id": "15530564",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jrottinghuis",
              "name": "jrottinghuis",
              "key": "jrottinghuis",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Joep Rottinghuis",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "body": "For late arriving data that was spooled using whatever we come up with in YARN-4061, we can still recognize records that came in after we got rid of the finalized application's last write.\nIf we can have the _first_ write marked as a special value, just like the final value is marked, then we can later on distinguish the case where we have a later-arriving update.\n\nAside from the very first record (marked special) we will always have an existing record that will slide in front of or behind exising values. In other words, we see either a new value and it is the first, or we see multiple values. We could use that to see if late values come in. The trick will be to see if we can do this after the fact ( in the read or flush compaction) rather than during writes. This may have to be a write-time copro that processes data only if it is later than the normal timewindow (more than a day old). For those cases we might have to do reads during writes, or at least mark records as suspicious for later analysis.",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jrottinghuis",
              "name": "jrottinghuis",
              "key": "jrottinghuis",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Joep Rottinghuis",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "created": "2016-09-28T19:07:04.277+0000",
            "updated": "2016-09-28T19:07:04.277+0000"
          },
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12928506/comment/15530597",
            "id": "15530597",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jrottinghuis",
              "name": "jrottinghuis",
              "key": "jrottinghuis",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Joep Rottinghuis",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "body": "All data that comes in late would be marked as suspicious. Only if accompanied with non-suspicious data will we keep this. If there is no other normal of final-value record we can discard this suspicious data.",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jrottinghuis",
              "name": "jrottinghuis",
              "key": "jrottinghuis",
